This Vintage OMEGA ref. 2710SC in solid 18K rosegold is in good unpolished condition. Movement no. 14xxxxxx dating it to 1954. The Omega automatic bumper caliber 354 is running on good amplitude and with good accuracy on the timegrapher (-3 to -20 sec./day, depending on position) , even though the service history is unknown. Case diameter is 35mm without crown and fancy lugs. Case and movement weight around 34 grams. Original dial and hands are in good vintage condition and are showing some patina throughout. Strap and buckel are not from Omega.
